</header><div class="entry-content" itemprop="text"><div class="at-above-post-homepage addthis_tool" data-url="http://humorwriters.org/2019/01/31/leigh-anne-jasheway/"></div>
<p><img class="alignright wp-image-11946" src="http://humorwriters.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/50832893_10217840786909660_7415149732466524160_o-400x400.jpg" alt="" width="275" height="275" srcset="http://humorwriters.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/50832893_10217840786909660_7415149732466524160_o-400x400.jpg 400w, http://humorwriters.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/50832893_10217840786909660_7415149732466524160_o-100x100.jpg 100w, http://humorwriters.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/50832893_10217840786909660_7415149732466524160_o-768x768.jpg 768w, http://humorwriters.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/50832893_10217840786909660_7415149732466524160_o-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, http://humorwriters.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/50832893_10217840786909660_7415149732466524160_o.jpg 1545w" sizes="(max-width: 275px) 100vw, 275px" /><a href="https://www.accidentalcomic.com/">Leigh Anne Jasheway</a> is a stress management and humor expert, comedy writer, stand-up comic and comedy instructor/coach.<br />
“I have an M.P.H. degree, which either stands for master’s of public health or mistress of public humor (and, occasionally, miles per hour, but only if I’ve had too many espressos). In lieu of actually getting a real job, I consult with organizations (and disorganizations) on how to use humor to manage stress, change and conflict and boost creativity, [&hellip;]<!-- AddThis Advanced Settings above via filter on get_the_excerpt --><!-- AddThis Advanced Settings below via filter on get_the_excerpt --><!-- AddThis Advanced Settings generic via filter on get_the_excerpt --><!-- AddThis Share Buttons above via filter on get_the_excerpt --><!-- AddThis Share Buttons below via filter on get_the_excerpt --></p>
